1 SECTION 2. If any provision of this act or its application to any person or
2 circumstance is held invalid, the invalidity does not affect other provisions or applications of this
3 act that can be given effect without the invalid provision or application and, to this end, the
4 provisions of this act are severable.
5 SECTION 3. The Secretary of State shall develop forms to implement G.S. 66-529,
6 as enacted by this act.
7 SECTION 4. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Office of Secretary
8 of State the sum of ten thousand dollars ($10,000) in recurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal
9 year to be used by the Office of Secretary of State to pay for the cost of registering consumer
10 legal funding companies.
11 SECTION 5. Section 4 of this act becomes effective July 1, 2026. The remainder of
12 this act becomes effective October 1, 2026, and applies to violations occurring on or after that
13 date.
